snippet.textDisplay: Look...not all cowboys fans are delusional. A lot of us know that even before Garrett, Jerry needs to go, (as far as how involved he is with the team). Not that I think that Jason Garrett is an exceptional coach, but he's definitely not a garbage coach. It may not have changed much, but if Jerry wasn't so involved, just maybe Garrett could have been his own coach. We'll never know. The cowboys lack a certain type of confidence where I think teams literally say before playing them, "we're not scared of them at all". They had a lot of talent this year, but in no way did I believe they were going to the superbowl. Might sound stupid, but they need to change the culture of the team before they even pretend to make/go far into the playoffs.
